sentences: Robert L. King (January 29, 1941 – July 22, 1983) was an American Chicago blues guitarist, singer and songwriter.
King worked with Hank Ballard and the Midnighters, Bobby Bland, Lee "Shot" Williams, Eddy Clearwater, Freddie King, Lonnie Johnson, The Aces and Sonny Thompson.
Following a violent altercation in a Chicago nightclub, King died from his injuries at the age of 42.
An obituary appeared in Living Blues magazine (issue No. 58) later that year.
